<item>
            <title>[DISTRELEC-3587] Meta Navigation: add login/logout link and user name</title>
                <link>https://jira.namics.com/browse/DISTRELEC-3587</link>
                <project id="10935" key="DISTRELEC">distrelec relaunch</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;User feedback has shown that the login functionality is not found by most users.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a quick win, a static CMS link &quot;Login&quot; was added to the meta navigation pointing to the login page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Suggested improvement:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add a dynamic link in the black area of the meta nav
	&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;if user is anonymous: Text = &quot;Login&quot;, target = login page&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;if user logged in: Text = &quot;Logout&quot;, target = login functionality, user stays on same page if no login required for it, or is taken to home page with logout success message&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add user name info on the left of the logout link, displays if user is logged in
	&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&quot;&lt;b&gt;Logged in as&lt;/b&gt; &amp;lt;first name&amp;gt; &amp;lt;last name&amp;gt;&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;DE: &quot;Angemeldet als&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;FR, IT: to be translated&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
